==English==
===Noun===
'''defective verb''' (''plural'' '''defective verbs''')

#(''grammar'') A [[verb]] that can only be conjugated in certain [[person]]s and [[number]]s, especially one that has no forms except for the [[third-person singular]].
#:''The verb "to snow" is a defective verb as it is only used in forms such as "it is snowing" - you can't say "I snow", for example.''

